<objective>
Third commit in the Wave 2 atomic-cutover quartet. Land the user_benchmark_percentiles schema reshape (PK widens to `(user_id, metric, time_control_bucket)`; ENUM reshapes to exactly 8 values per CONTEXT D-13; Recovery Score Gap rescues from v1 drop list per D-05a), rewrite the per-user percentile service to consume Plan 04's `COHORT_PERCENTILE_CDF` via Plan 02's anchors and Plan 03's per-TC builders, add the page-level ΔES chip aggregation helper at the API shaper layer per CONTEXT D-08 / D-08b, extend the API schema for anchor disclosure per RESEARCH Open Question 4, and retire the legacy `interpolate_percentile` + `GLOBAL_PERCENTILE_CDF` stubs that Plan 04 left in place.

Purpose: This plan is where the peer-relative architecture lights up end-to-end inside the backend. Plan 04 generated the COHORT_PERCENTILE_CDF and the helper; this plan wires per-user lookups against it, populates `user_rating_anchors` from Stage A via Plan 02's storage + Plan 01's conversion module, reshapes the per-user storage to match the new (user_id, metric, tc) granularity, and aggregates per-TC sub-percentiles into the page-level scalar that the API ships. After this plan, the backend is ready for Plan 06 to backfill the entire user base.

Output: 9 file changes (1 NEW migration, 2 model/repo reshapes, 3 service rewrites/extensions, 1 schema extension, 1 type regen, 2 test rewrites/extensions). After this plan, Plan 06 backfills against the new shape; Plan 07 (frontend) lights up the chip + tooltip rewrite consuming the new types.
</objective>

