<threat_model>
## Trust Boundaries

| Boundary | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| API → service → repository | Authenticated `current_user.id` from FastAPI-Users dep is the sole `user_id` source; never accepted as a query/path parameter (V4 mitigation, preserved). |
| Python → Postgres | Static SQL + bindparams + `Literal`-typed parameters preserve injection safety from Plan 03. |
| Service → external snapshot (ChessGoals) | `convert_chesscom_to_lichess` is a pure-Python lookup against the locked snapshot (Plan 01); no live HTTP call. |

## STRIDE Threat Register

| Threat ID | Category | Component | Disposition | Mitigation Plan |
|-----------|----------|-----------|-------------|-----------------|
| T-94.4-05-01 | Tampering | ENUM value injection via API | mitigate | All metric IDs and TC values produced by backend code; `fetch_for_user` filters by `user_id` only. New `RatingAnchorOut.source_platform` Literal-typed at the wire. |
| T-94.4-05-02 | Information disclosure | `fetch_anchors_for_user(user_id=...)` requires authenticated `user_id` per V4 | mitigate | `user_id` keyword-only; sourced from FastAPI-Users `current_user.id` dep. Same as Phase 94.1 / 94.2 / 94.3. |
| T-94.4-05-03 | Tampering | Destructive migration on prod loses data without recovery path | accept | Per CONTEXT D-02: `user_benchmark_percentiles` is non-critical product surface; `scripts/backfill_user_percentiles.py` (Plan 06) is the canonical recovery path. Migration docstring carries DESTRUCTIVE banner. PR description documents the recovery sequence. |
| T-94.4-05-04 | Tampering | Sentry message embeds variable data fragmenting issue grouping | mitigate | CLAUDE.md Sentry rule preserved: `sentry_sdk.set_context("percentile_compute", {"user_id": ..., "stage": "A/B", "metric": ..., "tc": ...})` followed by `sentry_sdk.capture_exception(exc)`. No variables in error messages. |
| T-94.4-05-SC | Tampering | npm/pip installs | accept | No new packages introduced in this plan; all dependencies (numpy, sqlalchemy, asyncpg, alembic, pydantic) already in `pyproject.toml`. |
</threat_model>

